<br>
First, let me say the &quot;play nice&quot; policy of Verant generally sucks. If you are camping... um... RCY in KC(fill in any camp) lets say, and my group comes and wants to &quot;share&quot; &quot;play nice policy&quot; says you have to share and that would suck because there wouldn't be enough mobs for us to spilt. We'd both wind up sitting on our asses not doing much, and stepping on each others toes. If you answer &quot;RCY is camped&quot; we wont come. You have a camp, and we don't want to share it or take it or bother anyone.<br>
<br>
Now if you had instead answered &quot;all of Karnors&quot; then I would have to think, well, any place you aren't at currently is open, so if we go to LCY and you aren't there, I don't feel bad about taking the camp.<br>
<br>
Same applies in sebilis for me, if you answer AoE group taking all of upper... I'm glad to contact you and work out a camp. If several other camps are taken and there is no room for us, we'll move along. If only one other camp is taken, I feel we have as much a right to be there as you. I am in no way saying we have MORE right to be there, only equal, we all have an equal right to play the game. I don't think one group has a right to take over an entire zone. We've (can't speak for everyone in the game because i'm not them, but MY group and any raid i've been on) always tried to work things out amiably.<br>
<br>
As a druid, I could easily go to CS (with a nice clarity) and &quot;claim&quot; 12 wyvern spawns, and keep them clean. But I don't because other people come and play and whoever gets to the mobs when they are up is welcome to them. Same with many other camps. Just because I have the ABILITY to claim a large area for my own, does not give me the right to do so.<br>
<br>
My feeling extend to AoE groups in the same way. You have the right to fight where you will, But please be understanding that we'd like to play too. We'll be glad to work things out with you, but I don't feel anyone has the right to claim large parts of any zone as their own, and doing so IS specifically mentioned in the rules for EQ.<br>
<br>
