<br>
Ah, hell, one more kick in the ribs won't hurt.<br>
<br>
AE groups are generally composed of good people, who know what they're doing, respect others, and are usually willing to help out regular groups with C3 or xlocs out or corpse drags.  They normally do their AEing during off hours, and they try not to interfere with other groups.  Every single time I've gone to Seb and found an AE group there, they've responded to my polite inquiry with &quot;sure, you can take NG, just give us five minutes to finish this spawn cycle, then it'll be clear.&quot;<br>
<br>
There are, of course, exceptions to this general statement.  There are AE groups who are exp-grubbing lootwhores who refuse to share anything.  There are AE groups who deliberately train other groups, and I'm sure that somewhere, there are AE groups who meet every week to wring the necks of adorable cuddly kittens while jerking off at their own l337ness.<br>
<br>
But y'know what?  Regular groups do all that too.  AE groups just get more negative attention because people are jealous of what they can do.  That's where the whining comes from, and the bitching, and the people who zone into Seb, see an AE group, then petition without bothering to talk to the group.<br>
<br>
Maybe I'm just dense, but where exactly is the problem with AE groups?  No AE group I've ever seen has been dumb enough to walk into a fully-camped Seb and say &quot;taking all of upper.&quot;  They normally get there first, when there's nobody in the zone.  So yeah, they kill everything in sight - who wouldn't?  When another group zones in, all they need to do is ask politely, and the AE group will usually give them a camp.  If the AE group doesn't want to share... well, boo-fucking-hoo, the regular group should port out and exp elsewhere... what's that?  You didn't invite a wizard into your regular exp group?  Your loss.  I'm sure the AE group will xloc you though, if you ask nicely.<br>
<br>
As for the whole &quot;they have no right to kill all the mobs&quot; thing, here's a little equation for you: ability + will = right.  If there's nobody else in the zone, they have undisputed right.  If another group comes in... well, does the other group have any more &quot;right&quot; just because it's made up of a cleric, warrior, chanter, gimp_00, gimp_01, gimp_02?  Fuck no.<br>
<br>
There's nothing wrong with AE groups in general.  Personally, I love sharing Seb with them - my casters get C3, we don't need to worry about repops up the ass, and hell, it's great to watch a good AE group in action.  If there's something wrong with a specific AE group or person, take it up with them personally.  Don't blame all AE groups for the faults of one or two bad apples.<br>
